<TEXT>
a singleengine plane that snagged a 
wire above a 500000volt power line crashed thursday afternoon 
killing three people and injuring a fourth 
the pilot of the frenchmade tb21 trinidad reported engine 
trouble shortly before the 213 pm crash near placerita canyon 
about 30 miles northwest of downtown los angeles the federal 
aviation administration said 
the survivor a teenage girl was in critical condition at henry 
mayo newhall memorial hospital in valencia said hospital 
spokeswoman ann ingram 
the pilot and two other passengers were killed none of the 
victims names was immediately released 
the fourseat plane hit a static wire which protects the power 
line from lightning said ed fraudenburg a spokesman for the los 
angeles department of water and power 
the plane missed the power line itself which carries enough 
electricity for the needs of 3 million people fraudenburg said 
dwp crews were assessing the damage to determine if the cable 
needs to be replaced fraudenburg said 
