be a yes or no answer means said i think theyre trying to 
pressure me to force me to enroll in a high school equivalency 
program i dont like being forced to do anything 
butch argued that the law was in conflict with another state law 
permitting students to drop out of school at age 16 the license 
suspension he said was condemning the teenager and his family to 
poverty because he was unable to earn the money he needed to support 
them without a drivers license 
means 16yearold wife tonya who is expecting a child in 
august also had her license suspended because she is a dropout 
deputy attorney general bruce wilson who represents the 
department of motor vehicles argued that revoking the decision to 
suspend means license would send the wrong message to other 
teenagers 
it will encourage those people who want to avoid their 
responsibility to the state and to themselves wilson said 
therese wilson of state department of education testified that 
since the law went into effect in the fall 1800 dropouts had 
returned to the classroom of that number 50 percent were still 
attending school in march 
in recent years the states dropout rate was about 17 percent 
or 5000 students she said the state expected to reduce the rate 
this year by 1000 students as a direct result of the law she said 
several states including wisconsin and texas where gov bill 
clements signed a dropout bill into law friday have passed similar 
legislation and others are considering such laws 
</TEXT>
