its sales agents jobs and pay millions of dollars to women who 
contended they were discriminated against from 1974 to 1987 
that lawsuit accused state farm of refusing to recruit women on 
the same basis as men for agent jobs and discouraging women from 
applying for the lucrative jobs according to the lawsuit although 
80 percent of all state farm employees in california were women 98 
percent of the agents were men 
