<TEXT>
the solidarity citizens committee which 
ran the unions campaign for the new parliament decided thursday 
not to disband now that elections are over patching a dispute that 
threated to split the opposition 
solidarity leader lech walesa and the unions national executive 
commission advocated closing the local citizens committee so that 
activists nationwide could concentrate on rebuilding the solidarity 
trade union itself 
but activists strongly disagreed and after a daylong debtate 
passed two vaguely worded resolutions that solidarity national 
spokesman janusz onyszkiewicz said meant local groups could continue 
to exist for now 
about 120 members of the national citizens committee set up in 
december by walesa to advise the union on political social and 
economic issues gathered in a warsaw university auditorium for the 
debate 
during the debate walesa defended a weekend resolution by the 
unions executive commission to concentrate efforts on rebuilding 
the east blocs first independent trade union which regained legal 
status april 17 
union organizing took a back seat during the election campaign 
but the final resolution thanked the local citizens committees 
which helped solidarity to its overwhelming election victory and 
said they should help prepare for free municipal elections a 
solidarity goal 
the executives resolution to dissolve the local committees 
should not be treated as something that should be implemented 
immediately onyszkiewicz said todays resolution says one 
should approach their transformation with flexibility he said 
the citizens committee is of the opinion that the main task at 
the present moment is expanding and strengthening the solidarity 
trade union and farmers solidarity as guarantors of democratic 
reforms in our country it said 
a 14member commission was appointed to present proposals on the 
future of the national citizens committee by sept 10 
walesa appeared concerned the continued existence of the 
committees would drain strength from rebuilding the union 
today if we get divided into two we weaken the most 
important stream and the most important stream today is the broad 
stream of working people he said 
a top adviser to walesa who opposed disbanding the committees 
tried to downplay conflict 
first of all we want to say in the current situation that we 
maintain unity that we are able to maintain it and that there is no 
conflict between the citizens committee and the bodies of the 
union said bronislaw geremek 
the weekend decision was greeted with anger from members of the 
local committees flush with their electoral triumph which saw 
solidarity win 99 of of 100 seats in the freely contested senate in 
june 4 and june 18 elections solidarity also won all seats 
available to it in the lower house the sejm 
critics said the decision was to prevent the committees in each 
of polands 49 provinces from becoming parallel possibly rival 
organizations to solidarity 
the dispute reflected contradictions within solidarity over 
whether it is ultimately a trade union or a political movement and 
whether it will be led by workers or intellectuals 
walesa has said solidarity should be mainly a union with 
politics eventually shifted to newly emerging political groups 
but solidarity nevertheless has a broad following among 
nonworkers students intellectuals and professionals who are 
more interested in pressing communist authorities for democratic 
political changes 
