bill to remove the remaining wellhead price controls from natural 
gas 
the housesenate compromise was cleared in the senate by a voice 
vote the house must take final action on the bill before it can be 
sent to president bush who is expected to sign it 
the legislation is designed to remove all federal price controls 
on natural gas by jan 1 1993 it is not expected to affect retail 
prices much because most gas under controls already is selling below 
the official ceilings 
the senates action came two days after house and senate 
negotiators agreed that gas from wells drilled after the date of 
enactment of the bil would be deregulated on may 15 1991 all other 
gas not already decontrolled would be freed from the federal 
ceilings when sales contracts are renegotiated or jan 1 1993 
whichever comes first 
about twothirds of the nations natural gas was freed from 
controls in 1978 
