herrmann whose speech was distributed by the governmentrun news 
agency adn said the peaceful student demonstrations in beijing 
were intended to be used for a counterrevolutionary overthrow of 
peoples power in china 
the politburo makes all key decisions in east germany and its 
report expresses the views of the countrys aging leaders led by 
erich honecker head of the party 
the party has strongly resisted sovietstyle economic and 
political reforms and herrmanns speech reaffirmed the countrys 
leading hardline position in the soviet bloc 
the politburo report said east germany will remain true to its 
own policies and made no hints at any reforms 
hungarys communist party and opposition groups have agreed to 
hold multiparty elections by next summer last week hundreds of 
thousands of hungarians turned out for an emotional reburial of imre 
nagy the communist leader executed after leading a revolt crushed 
by soviet troops in 1956 
under the flag of renewing socialism forces are at work that 
strive for the removal of socialism in this connection the 
developments in hungary fill us with great concern herrmann said 
he accused western leaders whom he did not identify of stepping 
up ideological and economic pressure on communist countries in an 
attempt to make them reject communism and turn to capitalism 
herrmann said the berlin wall will continue to protect east 
germany from economic plundering from the penetration of criminal 
elements and from drug smuggling 
