anemia the loss of red blood cells that 
can kill people who suffer malaria is largely caused by the bodys 
attempt to defend itself against the infectious disease research on 
mice suggests 
the lawrence berkeley laboratory study indicates overstimulation 
of part of the immune system also is partly responsible for other 
