the walt disney co has adopted a poison 
pill antitakeover defense but says it does not know of any 
prospective bids for the company 
the plan adopted by disneys board of directors and announced 
wednesday would entitle present stockholders to buy new stock at 
half price in the event of a hostile takeover attempt such plans 
dilute the holdings of a potential buyer making a buyout without 
management consent prohibitively expensive 
the plan is similar to those adopted at many american 
corporations in recent years and has been under consideration at 
disney for several months said spokesman tom deegan 
it was not as a result of anything that has happened in the 
