the united states came in for renewed criticism at 
world trade talks thursday for threatening unilateral action against 
countries accused of blocking us exports 
at a closed meeting of the general agreement on tariffs and 
trade the united states was also criticized for refusing to accept 
a ruling against us patent law but won praise for agreeing to 
ease restrictions on imports of sugar a gatt official said on 
condition of anonymity 
at the meeting the european economic community and norway both 
accepted gatt rulings that they should allow freer access to imports 
of fruit the official said 
