valley national corp of phoenix announced 
thursday it will add 181 million to its loanloss reserves and 
expects a 90 million loss in the second quarter as a result 
valley national bank of arizona and valley utah bancorporation 
are chief subsidiaries 
valley national chairman james p simmons attributed the action 
to a deterioration in arizonas real estate market with no immediate 
sign of recovery 
given that current market conditions make the estimation 
process difficult we believe we have taken a conservative view in 
determining the amount to be added to our reserves simmons said 
banks take such steps to protect themselves against the 
possibility that loans wont be repaid the weak property market in 
the economically depressed southwest has raised the risk of mortgage 
defaults 
valley national stressed that the corporations core earnings and 
financial base remain strong it projected that a substantial amount 
of the second quarter loss should be regained by the end of the 1989 
